WAVE COUPLING

wave_coupling is the coupling channel of the qu-septit native compute substrate
coupling is the strength of a body's connections to other bodies: high coupling means the body is firmly bonded to its neighbors, low coupling means it stands alone
coupling is what allows information to flow from body to body through the substrate

observe 0_quseptit.rana
observe fadriel_phase2.zc

the 7 properties of wave_coupling itself:
1 ENERGY zero
2 PHASE zero
3 SPIN zero
4 CHARGE neutral
5 COHERENCE zero
6 COUPLING one: this channel holds coupling primarily
7 OBSERVER zero

VERB carry_coupling
hold each body's coupling strength to its referenced neighbors

VERB strengthen_with_use
each successful interaction across a coupling slightly strengthens it
this is how heavily-used routes calcify into bones over time

VERB decay_with_neglect
couplings that have not carried information in a long time slowly weaken
this is how relationships fade if not maintained

a coupling channel is what makes the substrate a connected world rather than a collection of isolated points
without coupling, every body would be alone
with coupling, the substrate is a society
